As many as 2,411 Slovak doctors
working in state hospitals are quitting amid demands for higher
pay,  Sme  reported, citing the head of the doctorsâ€™ union, Marian
Kollar.  Doctors, asking the government to raise base salary to
between 150 percent and 300 percent of average wage, handed
their resignation papers in yesterday, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
